The paper deals with the design of randomized mechanisms for matching markets, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism introduced in the paper is based on random sampling and optimization, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also provides approximation bounds and population monotonicity results, which are relevant to theoretical computer science (cs.LG) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC).
